instructions:
Create a function `cleanUserData` that:
1. Removes extra spaces (trim)
2. Capitalizes first letter of name
3. Returns object: { name: cleaned name, valid: true if name not empty }

Example: '  john  ' ‚Üí { name: 'John', valid: true }

starterCode:
function cleanUserData(rawName) {
  // TODO: Complete all 3 tasks!
  // 1. Trim spaces
  // 2. Capitalize first letter
  // 3. Return object with name and valid status

}

solution:
function cleanUserData(rawName) {
  const trimmed = rawName.trim();
  if (trimmed.length === 0) {
    return { name: '', valid: false };
  }
  const capitalized = trimmed[0].toUpperCase() + trimmed.slice(1).toLowerCase();
  return { name: capitalized, valid: true };
}
